From: OnePlus Nord CE5 Kernel Workflow <kernel@local>
Date: 2026-06-08
Subject: [PATCH] mm/zram: fix broken hybrid_swap (RAM expansion) by NOT hijacking
 zram0 on OnePlus mt6897 (OOS16)

PROBLEM (observed on-device, dmesg/logcat):

    lowmemorykiller: /sys/block/zram0/hybridswap_meminfo open:
                     No such file or directory
    lowmemorykiller: Failed to parse swap info, But ignore!

ROOT CAUSE:

OnePlus/Oppo ship a FULL-SOURCE proprietary memory-compression driver
("hybridswap_zram") in the vendor tree
(vendor/oplus/kernel/mm/hybridswap_zram). It is compiled with Bazel as
the loadable module  oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko  and shipped inside
vendor_dlkm. That module is the ONE that registers /dev/zram0 on stock,
and it exposes OPLUS-private sysfs attributes used by userspace
(lowmemorykiller / "RAM expansion" / RSM), notably:

    /sys/block/zram0/hybridswap_meminfo   (zram_drv.c: DEVICE_ATTR_RO)

Its Kconfig is deliberately mutually exclusive with the upstream driver:

    config HYBRIDSWAP_ZRAM
        depends on BLOCK && SYSFS && HYBRID_ZSMALLOC && CRYPTO && !ZRAM

Consequently the OnePlus GKI common tree:
  1. comments out the upstream zram build in drivers/block/Makefile
     ("# obj-$(CONFIG_ZRAM) += zram/"), and
  2. ships CONFIG_ZRAM=m in gki_defconfig (ABI placeholder only).

so that the vendor module owns the "zram" block-major and the zram0 node.

THE BUG IN COMMUNITY KERNELS (incl. an earlier rev of this very tree):
to "make zram work", custom GKI/KernelSU builds force the UPSTREAM zram
driver in (CONFIG_ZRAM=y + uncomment the Makefile). On a device whose
vendor_dlkm still carries oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko, the built-in
upstream driver registers /sys/block/zram0 FIRST -- but WITHOUT the
hybridswap_meminfo attribute. The vendor module can then no longer own
zram0. Userspace opens /sys/block/zram0/hybridswap_meminfo and gets
ENOENT -> RAM expansion + hybrid swap are dead.

THE FIX:
Do NOT hijack zram0 from the vendor module. Keep the upstream zram driver
OUT of the GKI Image (Makefile entry commented, CONFIG_ZRAM=m, never =y)
exactly like stock, so the proprietary oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko from
vendor_dlkm remains the sole owner of /dev/zram0 and re-exposes
hybridswap_meminfo. This patch enforces that correct state (idempotent
no-op on a stock tree; reverts the anti-pattern on a tree that forced
upstream zram in).

This is a CONFIGURATION-level fix: the working zram/RAM-expansion stack
lives entirely in the vendor module (which our GKI Image's stable KMI is
compatible with -- every other vendor module loads fine on-device); the
GKI Image must simply stay out of its way.

---
--- a/drivers/block/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/block/Makefile
@@ -32,7 +32,9 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_DRBD)     += drbd/
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_RBD)     += rbd.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_PCIESSD_MTIP32XX)	+= mtip32xx/
 
-# obj-$(CONFIG_ZRAM) += zram/
+# zram0 is owned by the OPLUS vendor module oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko
+# (provides /sys/block/zram0/hybridswap_meminfo). Do NOT build upstream zram.
+# obj-$(CONFIG_ZRAM) += zram/	# keep DISABLED: vendor module owns zram0
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_RNBD)	+= rnbd/
 
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_NULL_BLK)	+= null_blk/
